Sometimes, there is a need to reuse any object, hence copy methods are always of a great utility.
Python in its language offers a number of ways to achieve this.
This particular article aims at demonstrating the copy method present in list.
Since list is widely used hence, its copy is also necessary.




Syntax : list.copy()




Parameters :
None





Returns :
Returns a shallow copy of a list.
Shallow copy means the any modification in new list wonâ€™t be reflected to original list